fdcsds (2.0.1-2) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Frontend: iPhone / small-viewport rendering fixes.
    - PageHeader now stacks below md (768px) so the h1, eyebrow, and
      description no longer wrap every word when action buttons compete
      for the row. `min-width: 0` on the titles column is the underlying
      fix; the mobile-drawer sidebar has been restored on <lg viewports.
    - DisksPage grids use `minmax(min(100%, N), 1fr)` so cards can shrink
      below the floor on narrow screens; every page inherits a shared
      `.fdc-page-body` responsive-gutter class.
  * Frontend: sidebar polish.
    - Chip pill gains `white-space: nowrap` so long labels like
      `UPDATE 2.0.1-RC1` no longer blow out the pill shape.
    - Sidebar `<nav>` scrolls internally on short viewports so the
      footer System card is always reachable.
    - System card now flows directly under the nav items (not
      bottom-anchored), giving consistent placement across pages; the
      update chip renders on its own left-aligned row with a new
      compact `size="sm"` variant.
  * Marked as `unstable` because this is a release candidate; will be
    promoted to `stable` for the 2.0.1 final tag.

 -- Joe Toppe <mreppot@gmail.com>  Sun, 05 Jul 2026 15:30:00 +0000

fdcsds (2.0.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * CP/M filesystem: adopt altair_tools' authoritative MITS 8" layout —
    correct sector skew, byte-7 data on data tracks, byte-4 checksum,
    8 allocation slots per directory entry. Files written by this
    version are now readable by real Altair CP/M, and files created by
    Lifeboat / MITS / Burcon CP/M can be read back cleanly.
  * CP/M filesystem: format-disk function + web UI (mount-guarded).
  * CP/M upload: raised multer ceiling to 8 MB and surface limit
    errors as clean JSON rather than a stack trace.
  * Reserve BIOS-opaque gap blocks so uploads don't clobber directory
    extensions on non-standard formats.
  * Drives: report NOT_READY on swap so FDC+ invalidates its track cache.
  * Build: derive Debian version from git so every commit produces a
    unique, monotonic .deb; require Node 22.
  * CI: dedicated release workflow that publishes the .deb to GitHub
    Releases on `v*` tag push.
  * Docs consolidated under docs/; retired obsolete planning files.
  * Marked as `unstable` because this is a release candidate; will be
    promoted to `stable` for the 2.0.1 final tag.

 -- Joe Toppe <mreppot@gmail.com>  Sat, 04 Jul 2026 18:00:00 +0000

fdcsds (2.0.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Initial Debian package release
  * Complete TypeScript rewrite of FDC+ Serial Drive Server
  * Features:
    - Serial disk emulation for Altair 8800
    - Multi-drive support (up to 4 drives)
    - Web interface with real-time monitoring
    - VT102 terminal emulator for serial console
    - REST API for remote management
    - Configuration file support
    - systemd integration
  * Includes sample disk images and comprehensive documentation

 -- Joe Toppe <mreppot@gmail.com>  Mon, 17 Nov 2025 00:00:00 +0000
